'''''Steve Davis Snooker''''' is a [[sports]] [[simulation]] [[video game]] developed and published by [[CDS Software]] in 1984. The budget release published by [[Blue Ribbon Software]]<ref name="MobyGames"/> reached the top of the UK charts in May 1988.<ref name='cvg81charts'>{{cite magazine |title=All Formats Combined Chart|magazine=Computer and Video Games|issue=81|publisher=EMAP|date=15 June 1988|page=|url=https://archive.org/details/cvg-magazine-081/page/n7/mode/2up|access-date=20 December 2021}}</ref> ''Steve Davis Snooker'' simulates the [[cue sports|cue sport]] [[snooker]]. Released under licence from 6-time [[Snooker World Championship|Snooker World Champion]], [[Steve Davis]].

The game is the first to feature a license of a professional snooker player, with later [[Jimmy White]] creating the [[Jimmy White's 2: Cueball|''Cueball'' series]].  CDS called the game the "ultimate successor" to their 1983 [[Pool (billiards)|pool]] simulator, titled ''Pool''.<ref name="Pool">{{cite web | url=https://www.giantbomb.com/images/1300-624718 | title=Spectrum Box Art | publisher=[[Blue Ribbon Software]] | work=[[Giant Bomb]] | access-date=January 17, 2018 | url-status=live | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118064623/https://www.giantbomb.com/images/1300-624718/ | archive-date=January 18, 2018 }}</ref> Davis would also be involved with the 1989 follow-up ''[[Steve Davis World Snooker]],''<ref>{{cite web|title=Steve Davis Snooker for Atari 8-bit (1985)|url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/atari-8-bit/steve-davis-snooker|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112160002/http://www.mobygames.com/game/atari-8-bit/steve-davis-snooker|archive-date=January 12, 2018|access-date=January 11, 2018|publisher=[[MobyGames]]}}</ref> as well as 1996's ''[[Virtual Snooker]].''

==Overview==
''Steve Davis Snooker'' allows players to play against themselves, or against a human opponent in either [[Snooker]], or [[Pool (billiards)|Pool]]. However, there is no opponent AI.<ref name="Commadore User Review">{{cite magazine | url=https://archive.org/stream/commodore-user-magazine-29/Commodore_User_Issue_29_1986_Feb#page/n35/mode/2up | title=Steve Davis Snooker Review | author=MacMahon, Ken | magazine=[[Commodore User]] | issue=29 | date=February 1986 | page=36 | url-status=live | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612122439/http://archive.org/stream/commodore-user-magazine-29/Commodore_User_Issue_29_1986_Feb#page/n35/mode/2up | archive-date=June 12, 2016 }}</ref> The game could be controlled by either a [[Gamepad|Joypad]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-steve-davis-snooker_6586.html | title=Atari 400 800 XL XE Steve Davis Snooker | work=atarimania.com | access-date=January 17, 2018 | url-status=live | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117011954/http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-steve-davis-snooker_6586.html | archive-date=January 17, 2018 }}</ref> or a [[Cursor (user interface)|Cursor]] and [[Computer keyboard|Keyboard]] control scheme.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0004896 | title=Steve Davis Snooker | publisher=World of Spectrum | access-date=January 17, 2018 | url-status=live | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117190453/http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0004896 | archive-date=January 17, 2018 }}</ref> The game has two different modes, with a ''short game'' (a game of Ten-Red Snooker similar to [[power snooker]]), or ''long game'', a game of traditional fifteen-red Snooker.<ref name=CRASH/>
[[File:Screenshot from Steve Davis Snooker.png|left|thumb|Screenshot from [[ZX Spectrum]] version. After potting a {{cuegloss|red ball}}, must nominate a {{cuegloss|colour ball|colour}} as above]]
The [[Atari]] game's box art boasts that the game has a "trick shot edit mode", "accurate spin", and "friction factor."<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-steve-davis-snooker_6586.html | title=Atari Box Art | publisher=CDS Software | work=atarimania.com | access-date=January 17, 2018 | url-status=live | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117011954/http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-steve-davis-snooker_6586.html | archive-date=January 17, 2018 }}</ref> 

